*24-02-2025*

CSS FLEXBOX:- *it's a short form of flexible-box
	      *it's one dimensional
	      *by default flexbox is responsive

CODE:--
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
    <head>
        <title>flexbox</title>
        <style>
            .parent{
                width: 100%;
                height: 100vh;
                display: flex;
                justify-content: flex-start;
                flex-direction: column-reverse;
            }
            .child{
                height: 200px;
                width: 200px;
                border: 1px solid black;
                color: white;
            }
            .c1{
                background-color: red;
            }
            .c2{
                background-color: blue;
            }
            .c3{
                background-color: green;
            }
        </style>
    </head>
    <body>
        <div class="parent">
            <div class="child c1">1</div>
            <div class="child c2">2</div>
            <div class="child c3">3</div>

        </div>
    </body>
</html>


**FLEX-BOX PROPERTIES**
*Display: flex;

*Justify-content:- flex-start, flex-end, space-event.

*Align-items:- flex-start, flex-end, center, stretch.

*Gap-it defines the gap between the html elements.

*Ex:- gap:20px;

*Order:- it specifies the order of html elements.

*Flex-grow:- it defines the expansion proportion of particular elements.

*Flex-shrink:- it defines the collapsion/compression.
	       default value:-1

*Flex-basis:- it defines the initial size of the elements.
	      default value:-auto

*Flex-basis:- 
